---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
import { organizationSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = `About: Why this site exists | ${SITE.name}`;
const description = `${SITE.name} is an independent resource for players in states where sweepstakes casinos were banned. Here's who we are and why we built it.`;
const crumbs = [{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'About', path: '/about' }];
---
<Base title={title} description={description} schema={[organizationSchema(), breadcrumbSchema(crumbs)]} canonical="/about">
  <Breadcrumbs crumbs={crumbs} />
  <article class="container-x py-10">
    <div class="prose-content mx-auto max-w-prose">
      <p class="mono-meta uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-head text-h1 text-ink">Why this site exists</h1>

      <p class="mt-6">
        I started following the sweepstakes casino space closely when the first ban bills appeared.
        What struck me wasn't the legal drama, it was the players left behind. State after state,
        millions of people who'd been playing legally woke up to find their platforms gone and no
        clear, trustworthy place to figure out what they could still do.
      </p>
      <p>
        The coverage that existed was either written for operators, or it was an affiliate farm
        dressed up as journalism, the kind of site that looks identical to the platforms it claims
        to review. None of it answered the simple question players were actually asking:
        <strong>what can I still legally play where I live?</strong>
      </p>
      <p>So I built this.</p>

      <h2>What we are</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} is an independent editorial resource. We track the legal alternatives to banned
        sweepstakes casinos, across every affected state, and we explain how each one stays legal,
        where it's available, and how much regulatory risk it carries. Think of it as a field guide,
        not a casino.
      </p>

      <h2>What we are not</h2>
      <p>
        We are not a casino, a gambling operator, or an operator-owned review site. We don't take
        money to rank a platform higher, and we don't hide the platforms with problems. When a
        platform's legal status is unconfirmed or shaky, we say so plainly, even when it would be
        more profitable not to.
      </p>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>
      <p>
        Some links on this site are affiliate links, meaning we may earn a commission if you sign up
        through them, at no cost to you. That revenue keeps the site independent and updated. It
        never changes our ratings or what we choose to list. You can read exactly how we handle this
        on our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a> and
        <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> pages.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Found something out of date? A platform changed status? A new alternative we should cover?
        Email me directly at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>. This
        space moves fast, and reader tips are one of the best ways we keep up.
      </p>

      <p class="mono-meta">By {SITE.author}</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
